    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-07-31</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-08-29T18:19:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Education Tax Deduction for All Act of 2008 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow parents of children attending an elementary or secondary school a tax deduction equal to: (1) 25% of their state's average public education per pupil expenditure for each qualifying student attending public school; and (2) 100% of such expenditure for each student attending any other school, including a home school. Allows taxpayers who do not otherwise itemize their tax deductions to claim such deduction. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Education Tax Deduction for All Act of 2008</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
